Open Questions
Tier 1
* What issues have caused the Board to decide that dissolving the institute is necessary? 
* What is the current legal status of the Ronin Institute? 
* What is the current capacity of the (former?) Board of Directors? Do they still legally represent Ronin as an Institute?
* What are the available paths forward for any current Ronin facilitated grant holders?
Tier 2
* Does the dissolution resolve the issues in any way or do they persist, and if so, how?
* What was the nature of the data incident - an act of sabotage, an attempt to help or something else entirely?  (what data incident??) See Appendix C. Data Breach Email 
* What happens to the digital assets or liabilities of the Ronin Institute[a][b][c][d][e][f][g][h][i][j][k] (e.g., internet domain registration, logo copyright, taxes, bank account, outstanding grants)?
* What are alternative not-for-profit 501(c)(3) organizations that will permit you to have PI status and accept Ronin's 10% de minimis Indirect Costs or 25% overhead with NSF?
Action Items (who is working on what)
(Jorrit/Daniel, done) Propose a framework to collaborate on ways to reframe Ronin and learn from this experience.


(ongoing) Set up round of meetings, and follow the standard Ronin Governance model step by step request members to vote on decisions see also CONSENSUS GOVERNANCE PROCESS AND TOOLS.






Immediate Goal
G0. Appreciate all the work that went into Ronin - the countless hours spent on keeping the organization alive, the effort put into resolving conflict, dealing with massive amounts of paperwork, and carrying the weight of unprocessed events and miscommunication. Despite all our differences, I believe we have many things in common, especially the pursuit of independent scholarship. (I am feeling a bit cheesy now, but I think I mean it. . . ). In short - figure out how to hit the "pause" button, thank each other and reflect.


G1. Confirm with the Board their decision to resign, and[l] determine the next steps for having formal leadership in place to make crucial decisions. An “interim board”? 
* Do we need to issue an acceptance of resignation letter and get as many scholar as possible to sign it?  Also, find out who owns /controls the digital resources (entered a to do item in the consensus doc)
* 



G2. Understand what the scope of the problem is. Host a listening session with the current board and any former Advisory Board members who are willing to attend. [m][n][o][p]
G1. Organize ourselves (highest priority), decide a governance structure and process, document the process 
G1. Follow  Consensus Model for Decision Making (see also https://www.sociocracyforall.org/sociocracy/)
  



