G2. Retaining services 
Here are the services that the Ronin Institute provides: 
1. Sponsored Research Office
2. Human Subjects Research ethics review (via Rutgers U.[v][w][x][y][z][aa][ab])
   1. History (from Arika): Exempt review was offered at Ronin without a cost to membership for about a year up until March 2023 (I was the HSR chair who did these exemptions), but it was a cost to Ronin and only provided benefits to the few people who used it. The easiest route here is to just pay Rutgers to do the reviews (Ronin still has this relationship with Rutgers active). 
   2. Opportunity: We charge a service fee (sliding scale?) for doing/managing these exempt reviews. 
3. Affiliation and membership (via the website). This affiliation has allowed members to obtain discounts on software and physical library access. 
   1. Current status: Website is owned by Jon Wilkins (previous Ronin Institute President). Admin is Dana Cohen and possibly others. ronininstitute.org
   2. Communication with each other and self-organization (via Slack)
4. Promoting the successes of our membership (via Newsletter and social media)
5. An email account for each member.


